OL,3,CTwo hospitals but just one decision
OL,4,Cover the closure of A&E services
OL,6,FThe first proposal brings children's
OL,7,Fand adult A&E together on a single
OL,8,Fsite at Southport Hospital, relocating
OL,9,Fthe children's A&E from Ormskirk
OL,10,FHospital and extending it to a 24-hour
OL,11,Fservice.
OL,13,FIt's estimated that option will cost
OL,14,F#33 million and take five years to
OL,15,Fcomplete.
OL,17,FThe second option sees services
OL,18,Fconsolidated at Ormskirk Hospital
OL,19,Finstead, relocating the adult A&E from
OL,20,FSouthport to Ormskirk and extending
OL,21,Fthe current children's A&E to 24 hours.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
