OL,3,CTwo hospitals but just one decision
OL,4,Cover the closure of A&E services
OL,6,FThis option is far more expensive,
OL,7,Festimated to cost #91 million and
OL,8,Fwould involve the transfer of seven
OL,9,Fservices including critical care. It
OL,10,Fwould take seven years to complete.
OL,12,FResidents speaking at the meeting
OL,13,Fvoiced concerns that hospitals are
OL,14,Funder enough pressure without putting
OL,15,Ftwo hospitals together:
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
